By adding a label that is unique to each facet

mpg |> 
  mutate(
    facet = case_when(
      drv == "f" ~ "front",
      drv == "4" ~ "4 wheel",
      drv == "r" ~ "rear"
    )
  ) |> 
  ggplot(
    aes(
      x = displ,
      y = hwy
    )
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap( ~ drv) +
  geom_text(
    aes(
      x = 4,
      y = 25,
      label = facet
    )
  )

fill controls background color.

  • angle: controls width of arrow head (smaller number is pointier)
  • length: length of arrow head (tip to base)
  • ends: "last", "first", or "both" - controls where to draw arrow head
  • type: "open" or "closed", type of arrowhead.
mpg |> 
ggplot(
    aes(
      x = displ,
      y = hwy
    )
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  annotate(
    geom = "segment",
    x = 4,
    y = 30,
    xend = 6,
    yend = 20,
    color = "red",
    arrow = arrow(
      angle = 50,
      length =  unit(0.25, "cm"),
      ends = "last",
      type = "open"
    )
  )

12.4.6

scale_color_gradient needs to be replaced with scale_fill_gradient

df <- tibble(
  x = rnorm(10000),
  y = rnorm(10000)
)

ggplot(df, aes(x, y)) +
  geom_hex() +
  scale_color_gradient(low = "white", high = "red") +
  coord_fixed()

ggplot(df, aes(x, y)) +
  geom_hex() +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "red") +
  coord_fixed()

  • labs takes a list of new name-value pairs, where the name should be an aesthetic (e.g.Â color).
  • The different scales take arguments that are passed on to continuous_scale
presidential |>

12.6.1

The parenthesis is necessary for patchwork to understand it should nest those plots. If omitted, it instead constructs the layout â€œcall-by-callâ€.

p1 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 1")
p2 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = drv, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 2")
p3 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = cty, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 3")

(p1 | p2) / p3

p1 | p2 / p3

p1 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 1")
p2 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = drv, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 2")
p3 <- ggplot(mpg, aes(x = cty, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  labs(title = "Plot 3")

p1 / (p2 + p3) +
  plot_annotation(
    tag_levels = "A", 
    tag_prefix = "Fig. ", 
    tag_suffix = ":"
  )
